  "text": "The convex problem (P ω ) is related to problems (C k ) and (R β ). So problem (P ω ) is a good tool for analyzing the combinatorial problems (C k ) and (R β ). This is used in sections 2 and 6. We remind that for any ω ⊂ I 0 N , the solution of problem (P ω ) is a (local) minimizer of the nonconvex objective F β in (3), see [CITATION_1] . This fact is independent of the value of β.",
